"title": "5199: womb",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5199: womb",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The part of the female body where offspring are conceived and developed. A barren womb can be indicative of God's displeasure or a test of faith, while a fruitful womb may be a sign of his favour. It is God who creates within the womb. In ancient Israel, the first offspring of every womb belonged to God.</p>\n<h2>The womb as the place of conception and gestation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:13-Ps139:16\">PSA 139:13–139:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:23-Gen25:24\">GEN 25:23–25:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:27\">GEN 38:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:53\">DEU 28:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:57\">DEU 28:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:10-Job3:12\">JOB 3:10–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:18-Job10:19\">JOB 10:18–10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:15\">JOB 31:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:9-Ps22:11\">PSA 22:9–22:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:5\">ECC 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:2\">ISA 44:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:24\">ISA 44:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:5\">ISA 49:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:7-Isa66:9\">ISA 66:7–66:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:14-Jer20:18\">JER 20:14–20:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:3\">HOS 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:41-Luke1:45\">LUK 1:41–1:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:4\">JHN 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:19-Rom4:21\">ROM 4:19–4:21</a></p>\n<h2>The barren womb</h2>\n<h3>Indicating divine displeasure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:18\">GEN 20:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:31\">GEN 29:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:11\">HOS 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:14\">HOS 9:14</a></p>\n<h3>As a test of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:6-Luke1:25\">LUK 1:6–1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:22-Gen30:23\">GEN 30:22–30:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:5-1Sam1:6\">1SA 1:5–1:6</a></p>\n<h3>A blessing in times of persecution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:29-Luke23:31\">LUK 23:29–23:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:19\">MAT 24:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:17\">MRK 13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:23\">LUK 21:23</a></p>\n<h2>A fruitful womb may indicate God's favour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:13\">DEU 7:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:31\">GEN 29:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:22-Gen30:23\">GEN 30:22–30:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:25\">GEN 49:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:4\">DEU 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:11\">DEU 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:9\">DEU 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:3-Ps127:5\">PSA 127:3–127:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps128:3-Ps128:4\">PSA 128:3–128:4</a></p>\n<h2>The first offspring of every womb belonged to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:1-Exod13:2\">EXO 13:1–13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:12\">EXO 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:15\">EXO 13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:15\">NUM 18:15</a></p>\n<h2>Proverbial use of the womb</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:21\">JOB 1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:34-Job15:35\">JOB 15:34–15:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:20\">JOB 24:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:8\">JOB 38:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:29\">JOB 38:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:3\">PSA 110:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:15-Prov30:16\">PRO 30:15–30:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:2\">PRO 31:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:15\">ECC 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:13\">HOS 13:13</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual life beginning in the womb</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:9-Ps22:10\">PSA 22:9–22:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:5\">PSA 51:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:3\">PSA 58:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:6\">PSA 71:6</a></p>",
